      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINTER MULWEE (8) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.03) at The Gardens behind Fascinate Jess in a Grade 5. Took the lead and boxed on but run over. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Rates highly and will give a great sight. BUMPY BLUE (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when seventh at Maitland over 400m behind Matt Jet Power (24.02) in a Grade 5. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Leading chance. TATOOINE (2) stuck on well last time to finish a neck back in second (20.83) at Nowra in a Grade 5 over 365m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Expected to be in the finish again. PINEAPPLE FRIDA (4) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
